Antoinette HELLER, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 5, 1937. Louis L. Swarthe and David Schwartz, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., of Los Angeles, Cal.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issued forthwith.
